comments.content: It looks sort of cobbled together. I seem to recall a while back someone posted a sample like this that was parts of Cezanne and various other scripts. The s is very familiar. The e looks like a start letter used out of place.
The best thing you could do is license P22 Cezanne and not go looking for this exact font as it is derivative and a knock-off.
